	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=244104"><span id=" ">Balmorra</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">5 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score:</span> Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>If you are running across the zone to fight in that zone somewhere have your pet guard where he is before you run.&nbsp;&nbsp;Then when you get to your camp use summon companion.  If you are just passing through zones either have him guard and he will zone with you anyway or just let him follow somewhere in the zone...he won't aggro anything.  I would recommend having summon companion up anytime you are travelling with a pet up...that way if your invis drops and you need to kill a mob in transit you can bring your pet to your side.  If you are using a &quot;slower than sow speed&quot; horse cast expedience on your pet and he will keep up fine.  Summon Companion is a level 39 spell.  If you don't have the spell yet i'd recommend you travel slowly through zones keeping your pet with you.  Making a new pet and equipping him takes too much mana when you get to your fighting location.  Starting a group oom as a mage kinda stinks.  As soon as you get there your prolly gonna start getting pulls, so having your pet ready will be a plus.<br/><br/><em id=fs8>Edited, Fri Mar  4 11:00:07 2005</em></p>&nbsp;<br /><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br />Balmorra Fleshburner<br/>Wizard on Drinal</td></tr>
